
if we don't want to commit and also not want to loose the content 
then we can do 

git add .
git stash


and whenever we wanted it back we can use
git stash pop


and we want to clear it that is permanently delete it we can use
git stash clear


git stash list  -> to list all stashed changesets.

git stash drop  -> this command discard the most recently changeset.


git stash pop  -> this command restore the most recently stashed file

git stash save -> this command temporarily stores all the modified tracked file



git show -> this command shows the metadata and content changes of the specified commit


git reset -hard [commit]  -> this command undoes all the commits after the specified commit and preserves the changes locally





git diff -> this command show the file difference which are not yet staged




